cast.overview: A spacecraft traveling to a distant colony planet and transporting thousands of people has a malfunction in its sleep chambers. As a result, two passengers are awakened 90 years early.
cast.title: Passengers

cast.overview: 70-year-old widower Ben Whittaker has discovered that retirement isn't all it's cracked up to be. Seizing an opportunity to get back in the game, he becomes a senior intern at an online fashion site, founded and run by Jules Ostin.
cast.title: The Intern

details.biography: Julee Cerda is an American actress born in Seoul, South Korea. She was raised in New York and spent part of her childhood in father's country in the Dominican Republic. She speaks fluent Spanish. She attended Marist College in Poughkeepsie, NY and currently resides in New York City. She is known for The Intern (2015), The Disappearance of Eleanor Rigby: Them (2014), and A Miracle in Spanish Harlem (2013).
details.name: Julee Cerda
